# Dual Format Output Rule

For every user instruction, always produce two artifacts in this order:

1. A complete Markdown file/content (`.md`) as the source of truth.
2. A complete HTML file/content (`.html`) generated from that Markdown.

## Consistency Requirements

- Content must match exactly between Markdown and HTML.
- Structure/format must match: headings, lists, tables, code blocks, links, and images.
- Paths must match: same directory, same basename, only extension differs.
- No omissions, no extra sections, no silent edits.

## HTML Requirements

- Must be a full HTML document: `<!DOCTYPE html>`, `<html>`, `<head>`, `<body>`.
- Must include `<meta charset="UTF-8">` and a proper `<title>`.
- Must include inline CSS for readable layout and default styling parity with Markdown rendering.
- Code blocks must use `<pre><code>` with monospaced styling.
- Tables, lists, and blockquotes must have explicit readable styles.
